This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) as it deals with wireless network virtualization and resource allocation. It could also belong to the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) as it involves the management of multiple virtual networks. Additionally, it could be classified under Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) as it deals with the allocation of resources in a shared infrastructure. Information Theory (cs.IT) could also be a possible sub-category as the paper involves optimizing the allocation of resources. Finally, it could be classified under Cryptography and Security (cs.CC) as the paper deals with the security of virtual networks.
